RelatedSentence: A federal judge moved up the July primaries to make sure there 's enough time for absentee voting in runoffs .
A federal judge moved up the July primaries to make sure there 's enough time for absentee voting in runoffs .
Election officials hope that does n't hurt voter turnout .
Election officials hope that does n't hurt voter turnout .
Election workers were busy all day setting up voting booths at the 28 precincts in Dougherty County .
Statewide , about 240,000 voters took advantage of early voting .
Less than 2,000 of Dougherty County 's 50,000 registered voters cast ballots early .
The elections supervisor is hoping for much better turnout tomorrow .

We would 've like to have seen more but hopefully tomorrow is the day that everyone has made up their mind and will turn out to those 28 precincts from 7:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m. to make that decision and cast their ballot , said Ginger Nickerson , Dougherty County Elections Supervisor .
